1.4 Creating & setting custom theme


theme_viny_bright <- function(){
  
  library(ggthemes)
  
  ggthemes::theme_fivethirtyeight() %+replace%
  
  theme(
    axis.title = element_text(),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 8),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 10),
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),
    plot.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),
    strip.background = element_blank(),
    legend.background = element_rect(fill = NA),
    legend.key = element_rect(fill = NA),
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,
                              size = 19,
                              face = "bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5)
      )
  
  }

theme_set(theme_viny_bright())

  labs(title = "Budget Estimate (Department of Agriculture, Cooperation & Farmers Welfare)",

1.6.4 % of Union Budget

agri_budget_share_plt3 <- agri_budget %>% 
  mutate(Agri_share_budget = round(Agri_Budget_est/Union_Budget_est, digits = 5)) %>% 
  
  ggplot(aes(x = Year, y = Agri_share_budget)) +
  geom_path(aes(group = 1), lty = 2, size = .9) +
  geom_point(aes(col = Party, shape = Party), size = 4) +

  geom_vline(xintercept = c(2014), col = c("grey"), lty = 2, size = .9) +
  
  labs(title = "% Share of Agriculture Budget est. in Union Budget est.",
       caption = "created by ViSa"
       # y = "Agri % Share in UnionBudget"
       ) +
  
  scale_y_continuous(
    # breaks = breaks_width(2000), 
    labels =  percent_format()) +
  
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size = 13),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 9),
    axis.title.y = element_blank(),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 9),
    text = element_text(size = 10),
    legend.position =  "none",
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
    axis.text.y = element_blank()
  ) +
  
  geom_text(size = 3 ,aes(x = Year, y = Agri_share_budget + .0009,
                label = scales::percent(Agri_share_budget))
            )

1.6.12 Box plot

final_4_agri_budget_plt <- agri_budget %>% 
  mutate(Agri_share_budget = round(Agri_Budget_est/Union_Budget_est, digits = 5)) %>% 
  
  ggplot(aes(x = Party, y = Agri_share_budget, fill = Party)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  
  labs(title = "Agri. Budget % Proportion in Union Budget",
       caption = "created by ViSa"
       ) +
  
  scale_y_continuous(
    # breaks = breaks_width(2000), 
    labels =  percent_format()
    ) +
  expand_limits(y = .0225) +
  
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size = 13),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 9),
    axis.title.y = element_blank(),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 9),
    text = element_text(size = 10),
    legend.position =  "none",
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
    # axis.text.y = element_blank()
  ) +
  
  annotate(geom = "curve", x = 1.5, y = .0195, curvature = .2, 
           xend = 1, yend = .0183, arrow = arrow(length = unit(2, "mm"))) +
  
  annotate(geom = "text", x = 1.5, y = .019, label = "Average/Median \n of agri share\n in Budget", hjust = "left")

1.6.13 Regression plot

agri_budget_plt6 <- agri_budget %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Year, y = Agri_Budget_est, col = Party)) +
  # geom_path(aes(group = 1), arrow = arrow(type = "closed")) +
  geom_point(size = 4, aes(shape = Party, col = Party)) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = c(2014), col = c("midnightblue"), lty = 2, size = .9) +
  
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = TRUE, fullrange = TRUE, level = 0.95) +
  
  labs(title = "Agri Budget Growth Trends wrt to govt. ",
       subtitle = "(using Regression lines for respective govts.)",
       caption = "created by ViSa"
       # y = "Agriculture Budget Est. (Cr)"
       ) +
  
  scale_y_continuous(
    # breaks = breaks_width(2000), 
    labels =label_dollar(prefix = "\u20b9", suffix = " Cr"),
    limits = c(0, 60000)
    ) +
  
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size = 13),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 9),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 9),
    text = element_text(size = 10),
    # legend.position =  "none",
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
    axis.title.y = element_blank()
    # plot.subtitle = element_text(size = 7)
  )
